bug.short_desc: testrunner does not work properly in Chrome browser

long_desc.thetext: Created attachment 1163 screenshot for the testrunner bug
That's strange. Which version of Chrome are you using? Do you get the same problem in the online Test Runner (http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/testrunner/)?

It works fine with the mentioning demo testrunner.
But this bug is highly reproducible. I can reproduce it very reliably.
1. just download clean qooxdoo sdk 1.6 2. creation-application.py ... 3. generate.py test 4. cd test 4. python -m SimpleHTTPServer 5. open Chrome and goto http://localhost:8000/ 6. try click on the "Log Level" button
(In reply to comment #2) > That's strange. Which version of Chrome are you using? Do you get the same > problem in the online Test Runner > (http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/testrunner/)?
Just try the same step on ubuntu, same result with windows. Definitely a bug.
This might be caused by the issue described in bug #6063.

(In reply to comment #4) > Just try the same step on ubuntu, same result with windows. > Definitely a bug.
That might have been a bug. We gave it a try with the current master and could not reproduce it. Could you maybe check if you can reproduce it with the current master? If so, reopen the issue and let us know.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
